cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques applied to biomedical data. Specifically, it focuses on word sense disambiguation using knowledge-based approaches and neural concept embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also employs machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The use of concept embeddings and distant supervision suggests that the paper may also fit into cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on representation learning and neural networks makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
